@startuml PY-007-sequence
title PY-007 — Password Checker · Sequence: Learner Completes Project → Badge Awarded

actor Learner
participant "ProjectShell\n«client»" as Shell
participant "useSkillProgress\n«hook»" as SkillHook
participant "getProjectData()\n«lib»" as GetData
participant "pj-1.md\n«content»" as Content
participant "ProjectCodePanel\n«client»" as CodePanel
participant "pyodide.runCode()\n«lib»" as Pyodide
participant "useProjectProgress\n«hook»" as ProjHook
participant "Supabase" as DB

== Page Load ==

Learner -> Shell : navigate to /projects/pj-1
Shell -> SkillHook : isUnlocked("pj-1")?
SkillHook -> DB : read skill completion for learner
DB --> SkillHook : variables=easy✓  conditions=easy✓
SkillHook --> Shell : unlocked = true

Shell -> GetData : getProjectData("pj-1")
GetData -> Content : read markdown
Content --> GetData : { scaffoldedCode, solution,\n  expectedKeywords, instructions }
GetData --> Shell : ProjectData

Shell --> CodePanel : render(scaffoldedCode)
CodePanel --> Learner : editor pre-filled with starter code

== Attempt Loop ==

loop until correct or attempts = 3

  Learner -> CodePanel : edits code + clicks Run
  CodePanel -> Pyodide : runCode(learnerCode)
  Pyodide --> CodePanel : { output, rawError }

  alt rawError present
    CodePanel --> Learner : friendly error message (PY-003 flow)
  else output present
    CodePanel -> CodePanel : validate(output, expectedKeywords)

    alt output passes keyword check
      note right of CodePanel
        Checks that output contains
        at least one of: "weak", "okay",
        "strong" — case-insensitive
      end note
      CodePanel -> ProjHook : markComplete("pj-1", xpReward=200)
      ProjHook -> DB : upsert project_completions\n{ learnerId, projectId, completedAt, xpEarned }
      DB --> ProjHook : saved
      ProjHook --> CodePanel : confirmed
      CodePanel --> Learner : ProjectBadge 🔒 + XPRewardBanner (+200 XP)\n+ ConceptSummary revealed in left panel
    else output fails check
      CodePanel -> ProjHook : incrementAttempts("pj-1")
      ProjHook --> CodePanel : attempts = n

      alt attempts >= 3
        CodePanel --> Learner : "Show solution" button appears
      else attempts < 3
        CodePanel --> Learner : "Not quite — try again" message
      end
    end
  end

end

== Solution Reveal (if triggered) ==

Learner -> CodePanel : clicks "Show solution"
CodePanel --> Learner : solution code replaces editor content\n(read-only view, no badge awarded)

@enduml
